1.title: Pilot
1.plot: She starts writing in her diary. Her first entries as a preteen girl are about her love for Justin Bieber, cupcakes, and Twilight.

2.title: Sept 4th 2012
2.plot: On the first days of high school, she bumps into Jessica.

3.title: Sept 5th 2012
3.plot: Her locker is reassigned next to Jessica's. She remembers how they both met.

4.title: Sept 6th 2012
4.plot: She remembers why Jessica stopped hanging out with her in middle school.

5.title: Sept 7ht 2012
5.plot: She twists her ankle on the way to class. She is 10 minutes late.

6.title: Sept 8th? 2012
6.plot: She describes her dream of the mask and the bee.

7.title: Sept 10th 2012
7.plot: She goes to Bobby's pool party where she is the victim of a food fight started by Bobby. She spends some time with Jessica.

8.title: Sept 11th 2012
8.plot: She hears rumors about Jessica in the girls' locker room.

9.title: Sept 12th 2012
9.plot: She sneaks into school at night to look for Jessica's school records. The next day, she hears a new rumor about her that would keep her from coming back to school. Bobby apologizes to her.

10.title: Sept 13th 2012
10.plot: A third rumor spreads out relating Jessica's disappearance to the absence of a substitute teacher.

11.title: Sept 14th 2012
11.plot: A teacher confirms some of the rumors related to Jessica not coming back to school. She goes to the movies with Bobby and his friends.

12.title: Sept 15th 2012
12.plot: She chats with Bobby after their movie date. She finds out about his family history and discovers a disturbing fact about his family.

13.title: Sept 17ht 2012
13.plot: She confronts the teacher that confirmed one of the rumors. A fourth rumor that explains Jessica's disappearance and involves Bobby's pool party comes out.

14.title: Sept 18th 2012
14.plot: She goes to Jessica's house and finds her crying on the floor, next to the dead body of a man.

15.title: Sept 18th 2012 Part II
15.plot: Her mom reads the last entry in her diary and calls the police. She notices Bobby riding a bike.

16.title: Sept 19th 2012
16.plot: In order to help Jessica, she must become her.

17.title: Sept 19th 2012 Part II
17.plot: She asks Bobby to help her alert Jessica that the police are on their way. She explains how Jessica and her attempted to move the body to the basement. And confronts her mom about why she read her diary.

18.title: Sept 20th 2012
18.plot: She sneaks out of her house at night to check up on Jessica. She talks about Jessica's dad's illness. She watches KittenCam on YouTube.

19.title: Sept 21st to 22nd 2012
19.plot: Jessica's story appears in the evening news. Jessica hides at her house. They discuss her dad's illness and the insurance company.

20.title: Sept 23rd 2012
20.plot: She hangs out with Jessica at the park, where Jessica finishes sharing the story of her dad's illness, and an accident involving a gun.

21.title: Sept 24th 2012
21.plot: The preparations for the Homecoming Dance begin at school. Jessica's story is on the evening news again, some contradicting details are reported.

22.title: Sept 25th 2012
22.plot: She gets a paper note from Bobby. She talks about all the things she should be looking into to get ready for the Homecoming Dance.

23.title: Sept 27th 2012
23.plot: She spends two nights in jail after being arrested.

24.title: Sept 28th 2012
24.plot: She is encouraged to tell her story to the police or else they would have to get the information out of her diary.

25.title: Oct 1st 2012
25.plot: She ponders upon different ways to get rid of the diary permanently.

26.title: Oct 2nd 2012
26.plot: Jessica hands the diary to her mom and copies are made for the police to review.

27.title: Oct 3rd 2012
27.plot: Her diary confession sets her up as the number one suspect. She will be on trial for murder.

28.title: Oct 4th 2012
28.plot: During her trial, her mom testifies against her. She discovers a very surprising fact about Jessica.

29.title: Oct 5th 2012
29.plot: She was found guilty, but will not be going to jail. She is sent to a mental facility instead.

30.title: July 3rd 2014
30.plot: Two years later, she is released from the mental facility. Her mom tracks Jessica down to invite her to pick her up.

1.title: Sept 8th 2014
1.plot: A new school year begins. She is placed one year behind Bobby, who now has a new girlfriend.

2.title: Sept 12th 2014
2.plot: She devises a ploy to break Bobby and his cheerleader girlfriend up.

3.title: Sept 15th 2014
3.plot: Bobby's girlfriend breaks up with Bobby for other reasons. She befriends the goth kids.

4.title: Sept 16th 2014
4.plot: Bobby is now single, but still not approaching her. She gets advice from one of her goth friends.

5.title: Sept 17th 2014
5.plot: She dyed her hair blonde and auditions for the cheerleader squad.

6.title: Sept 18th 2014
6.plot: She gets asked out by other people. Also, finds her AP Psychology teacher very attractive.

7.title: Sept 19th 2014
7.plot: The psychology teacher uses her as an example in class.

8.title: Sept 21st 2014
8.plot: She goes to Bobby's football game. Then Bobby asks her to go bowling.

9.title: Sept 22nd 2014
9.plot: She compares the layout of her school to that of the psychiatric ward.

10.title: Sept 23rd 2014
10.plot: Bobby gets back together with his girlfriend. Mr. Morgan starts dating. She has a decision to make.

11.title: Sept 24th 2014
11.plot: She talks about how Bobby and Mr. Morgan being taken affects her love life and how it feels like this will be a bad day.

12.title: Sept 25th 2014 2nd Period
12.plot: She talks about how during the second period, one of her goth friends, Rocco, was missing. She fears something bad may have happened to him.

13.title: Sept 25th 2014 3rd Period
13.plot: During the 3rd period she looks for Rocco, but couldn't find him.

14.title: Sept 25th 2014 5th Period
14.plot: She finally finds Rocco at Mr. Morgan's class. Bobby joins the class too. A crime involving a gun breaks out.

15.title: Sept 25th 2014 Part IV
15.plot: School security rushes in to help stop the crime. Rocco is taken to jail. An ambulance takes the victims to the hospital.

16.title: Sept 26th 2014: Part 1
16.plot: The two victims, Bobby and Mr. Morgan, are in great danger. They may not survive. She might be able to help only one of them.

17.title: Sept 26th 2014 Part II
17.plot: She describes how it felt like to witness the significant others of the victims waiting in the waiting room and volunteering to help only one of them in front of both families.

18.title: Sept 26th 2014 Part III
18.plot: She wonders if the way the decision on whom she will help survive was fair, since one of the significant others helped her decide.

19.title: Sept 26th 2014 Part IV
19.plot: Realizing it is not fair to let one of them die, she decides to sacrifice herself for them, since it was her fault all of this happened in the first place.

20.title: Sept 20est 2014
20.plot: She feels trapped inside something similar to a crematory and has time to review her actions and motives. She tries to exonerate herself from the blame.

21.title: Oct 6th 2014
21.plot: She explains how the doctors saved her life after losing all that blood, and talks about an update on the status of Bobby and Mr. Morgan. She explains that her life was saved by an anonymous donor.

22.title: Oct 9th 2014
22.plot: She talks about her favorite new show "24" and what happened when she returned to school. She sees Bobby for the first time after the attack.

23.title: Oct 10th 2014
23.plot: She finds her mom crying in the attic. Her mom was hiding something that peaked her interest. At night, she returns to the attic to find what it was.

24.title: Oct 11th 2014
24.plot: She talks to her mom about the object she found in the attic. Her mom explains the mystery behind the anonymous donor. But she discovers more to the story than she expected.

25.title: Oct 12th 2014
25.plot: She wants to go back to the attic to find more information to confirm her new findings, but Mr. Morgan shows up to get her caught up on his status. She then goes back to the attic and finds a journal with more information.

26.title: Jan 18th 2002
26.plot: The journal explains a horrifying past that she had blocked out regarding her donor.

1.title: Jan 12th 2015
1.plot: Winter break is over. She is already serving time in detention and feeling sorry for herself, when she notices that someone from her past is back in her life.

2.title: Jan 13th 2015
2.plot: During lunch period, she sits and stares at Jessica and wonders about why she is back and why hasn't she come talk to her. She notices a post-it left on her diary.

3.title: Jan 14th 2015
3.plot: Another day, another detention hour. But as she leaves school, she notices a guy in the library photocopying a book with a very intriguing title. She googles it to figure out what it could be all about.

4.title: Jan 15th 2015
4.plot: She plays with the cutest German shepherd on her way back from school. This memory is strangely stored in her mind. The puppy feels sick, and some guys from school approach her outside her house.

5.title: Jan 15th 2015 Part II
5.plot: The guys that met her outside her house had no good intentions. They asked her about the book they were photocopying she ends up with a bloody nose.

6.title: Jan 16th 2015
6.plot: Mr. Morgan debuts an original song on YouTube. She looks more into the book. And she hears that Bobby wants to talk to her.

7.title: Jan 19th 2015
7.plot: She has her first face to face with Jessica, since she returned. The owner of the dog informs her she will be moving away. Someone at school got in a fight.

8.title: Jan 20th 2015
8.plot: She helps the owner of the dog to find apartments in the new place where she is going.

9.title: Jan 21st 2015
9.plot: She realizes there was a post-it on her diary again, from the day before. But she starts feeling guilt for some of the things she has done.

10.title: Jan 22nd 2015
10.plot: She notices some activity at school where money is being passed down from classmate to classmate. Jessica distracts her to talk about Mr. Morgan's video.

11.title: Jan 23rd 2015
11.plot: Turns out Jessica wasn't talking about Mr. Morgan's first video, there was a second video. One where he is angry; at his followers, but especially at her. She gets the dog passed on to her as her neighbor moves away.

12.title: Jan 26th 2015
12.plot: She has her first real conversation with Jessica, where they try to understand the origins of the post-its that have been left on her diary.

13.title: Jan 27th 2015
13.plot: She takes Jessica to an interview with a guy that they think will help them solve the mystery of the book and the money being passed around in school. She remembers what it's like to have Jessica as a friend again.

14.title: Jan 28th 2015
14.plot: She wakes up to find out classes were canceled due to an attack that occurred during the night.

15.title: Jan 29th 2015
15.plot: Everybody at school is trying to find out who is part of the mob of students that attacked the school. She hears from Jessica that Bobby wants to ask her to be his prom date.

16.title: Feb 2nd 2015
16.plot: She spends the day with Jessica, but ends up seeing something that makes her doubt if Jessica is with her to be her friend again or for something else.

17.title: Feb 4th 2015
17.plot: Bobby finally catches up to her and asks her to be his date for the prom.

18.title: Feb 5th 2015
18.plot: Someone stalks her from the sidewalk outside her house, through the window. She holds her German shepherd to protect herself and tries to find out who that might be.

19.title: Feb 7th 2015
19.plot: She takes her dog out to the park where she shares his name with some people who didn't appreciate it. Then she is attacked by another dog.

20.title: Feb 9th 2015
20.plot: Something bad has happened to Pukey Face.

21.title: Feb 10th 2015
21.plot: She hears some bad news from her mom. Someone form her past is coming back and this time, it's not a good thing.

22.title: Mar 6th 2015
22.plot: She notices Jessica doing something unexpected, so she follows her. That ends up in an awkward situation.

23.title: Mar 24th 2015
23.plot: She visits Bobby. Bobby has a dark secret that he is not willing to share, but she discovers it anyway.

24.title: Apr 7th 2015
24.plot: She starts recounting how many people she needs to be on the look out for in order to feel safe. But coming out from the movie theater, she notices someone follows her out.

25.title: Apr 7th 2015 Part II
25.plot: She has a close encounter with the most dangerous character from her past. She also discovers that Mr. Morgan has been missing for a really long time.

26.title: Apr 29th 2015
26.plot: Since her encounter with Rocco, Jessica has volunteered to stay with her to protect her.

27.title: Apr 30th 2015
27.plot: She is out walking with Jessica at a park, when all of a sudden, Jessica falls to the ground. Rocco reveals himself and Bobby appears on the opposite side. An epic battle is about to unleash.

28.title: May 1st 2015
28.plot: Bobby and Rocco fight it out and only one of them survives the fight.

29.title: May 15th 2015
29.plot: Jessica wakes up in the hospital with a scar and some mental damage. Mr. Morgan's fate is revealed.

30.title: May 23rd 2015
30.plot: Prom night. Is she on her way to prom as Bobby's date and having the night of her life? Or does some one else have different plans for her?

1.title: May 24th 2015
1.plot: On the way to prom, Jessica notices something is off about her, it's almost as if she isn't quite who she says she is. This makes Jessica realize, they are both in real danger and she must act quickly.

2.title: May 25th 2015
2.plot: She explains how she manages to survive the fire with a little bit of luck, a little bit of pain, and a little bit of help from her best friend, Jessica.

3.title: May 27th 2015
3.plot: After the fire, she is treated in the hospital. Jessica helps her escape so they can make it to Mr. Morgan's funeral, but she never quite makes it to give her condolences to the Arts Teacher.

4.title: May 28th 2015
4.plot: The police show her a recording of what Rocco and her sister did to Mr. Morgan on the day of his murder in hopes that she can provide assistance in the investigation.

5.title: May 29th 2015
5.plot: She confronts her mom about some discrepancies in the information she told her and to the information in her dad's journal. Her mom recounts what happened on the day her dad died and the days shortly after.

6.title: June 5th 2015
6.plot: Bobby comes to visit her because he is looking for her sister and is unable to find her. Since they are twins, she seems to be next best thing. She gives him an earful about the consequences after being found out about his crime.

7.title: June 6th 2015
7.plot: She spends her birthday wondering about some big questions related to her sister and how little she remembers of her. Jessica helps her dig deep through some hypnosis methods.

8.title: June 7th 2015
8.plot: Jessica and her go to a night club to celebrate her birthday. They get hit on by mostly everyone, including Bobby and his friends, which drives them away, and they get in an accident.

9.title: June 8th 2015
9.plot: The doctors take Jessica into the OR and call her time of death. She does not take this like a normal person and does whatever it takes to keep the doctors trying to save Jessica.

10.title: June 10th 2015
10.plot: She had to deal with the consequences of helping Jessica through criminal ways, dealing with the hospital's lawyers.

11.title: June 11th 2015
11.plot: While Jessica is in a coma in the hospital, she reads a letter to her about how she feels about her situation and to encourage her not to give up, as the worst is still to come.

12.title: June 13th 2015
12.plot: She explains that Jessica will be OK thanks to some doctors that came in and saved the day. Of course she couldn't do this alone, she had Bobby's help, which did not come cheap.

13.title: June 20th 2015
13.plot: She has a run-in with the police, which gives her an idea on how to find her sister. In order to do so, she must enter the school's video department. She decides the Arts Teacher can help her, so she plans to meet with her.

14.title: June 21st 2015
14.plot: She visits the Arts Teacher and she turns out to be a mess after the death of Mr. Morgan. But through this visit, she identifies who is responsible for Jessica's tragic car accident that almost costed her her life.

15.title: June 22nd 2015
15.plot: She plots how to take revenge on the one responsible for Jessica's car accident. Visiting the Arts Teacher a second time, she opens up about Mr. Morgan changing and becoming violent days before his murder.

16.title: June 24th 2015
16.plot: Jessica wakes up from her coma. She wonders if she is being too harsh on the one responsible for Jessica's accident, but Jessica is in excruciating pain. So she reveals her plan which involves a trip to Latin America.

17.title: June 25th 2015
17.plot: Bobby comes to collect his price for helping Jessica, but he comes asking for more than what they agreed on. She tries to put a stop to it, but Bobby tells her the story Timothy, a little kid who ended up with broken jaw.

18.title: June 26th 2015
18.plot: She finally gets a chance to talk to Jessica after waking up from the coma. Since she is leaving for South America, she decides to leave the diary with Jessica to keep her company.

19.title: Aug 9th 2012
19.plot: Jessica writes in the diary a story from the past about a night she fought with her dad and took a bus to a random place.

20.title: Aug 9th 2012 Part II
20.plot: Jessica tells the story of the intruder that comes into her room and sexually assaults her, they even misfire a gun that hits her in the side of the leg. Her dad manages to scare the attacker away.

21.title: Aug 22nd 2012
21.plot: Jessica feels unsafe in her own house now, so she pleas with her dad to move away to another city. Her only hope is that her attacker isn't watching her and follows her wherever she goes.

22.title: Sept 9th 2012
22.plot: Jessica describes a story involving Bobby's pool party that sounds a little too familiar. After it, she finds her attacker and gets revenge.

23.title: Sept 9th 2012 Part II
23.plot: She walks into Jessica's abandoned house and finds Jessica there with the dead body of her attacker. They plot together what to do to take care of it in a way that Jessica doesn't have to end up in prison.

24.title: Sept 17ht 2012 and July 3rd 2015
24.plot: Jessica and her come up with a plan to trick everyone into thinking she had committed the murder, and that Jessica was never there. This would require a careful story planning written down in her diary.

25.title: July 4th 2015
25.plot: She returns from South America and explains how she collected what she needed for her revenge. She also met a new person, someone charming, but much older, Craig.

26.title: July 5th 2015
26.plot: She executes her revenge plan, but wonders if it was really necessary, or even if she will regret it eventually.

27.title: July 6th 2015
27.plot: After she returned from South America, Jessica committed suicide, so she confronts her. Jessica reveals it wasn't her, someone else did it to her. She checks the hospital's surveillance cameras, and finds out who did it.

28.title: Jul 7th 2015
28.plot: Jessica will need a surgery and blood transfusion to fight off an infection after her suicide. She decides to be the one who gives her the blood, but this is a tough decision for her.

imdb.plot outline: A 15 year old girl reunites in high school with Jessica, her better looking, more confident, childhood friend. Jessica suddenly goes missing, and the entire school starts making inappropriate rumors about what happened to her. Determined to find the truth, she discovers that Jessica has been harboring a deadly secret. But it all goes south when her loyalty to Jessica gets her in serious trouble, and their story is written down in her diary.
imdb.title: The Diary
plot: A 15 year old girl reunites in high school with Jessica, her better looking, more confident, childhood friend. Jessica suddenly goes missing, and the entire school starts making inappropriate rumors about what happened to her. Determined to find the truth, she discovers that Jessica has been harboring a deadly secret. But it all goes south when her loyalty to Jessica gets her in serious trouble, and their story is written down in her diary.::P.M. Salazar

Season 2: Following where season 1 left off, she returns to school, now an infamous character. She quickly gets involved with the wrong crowd and ends up in a love triangle between a friend and a teacher. The situation seems hopeless for her until a tragedy occurs to them on school grounds and she seems to be the only one that can help them survive. Their story is written down in her diary.::P.M. Salazar

Season 3: Following where season 2 left off, she runs into a classmate with a devious plan. She accidentally discovers more information than it would be safe to know, and that puts her in the middle of the turmoil. Also, Jessica is back in school, and together they try to figure out what this plan is all about, but a character from their past returns with vengeance on his mind. Their story is written down in her diary.::P.M. Salazar

Season 4: Following where season 3 left off, she is confronted by the police for a murder that occurred where she appears on camera. Along with Jessica, she tries to live a normal life as much as she can, but they have an accident that puts Jessica's life in danger. She will not let what happened to Jessica take her away from her, or let this go unpunished. So she takes a dive into her darkest self and their story is written down in her diary.::P.M. Salazar

Season 5: Following where season 4 left off, she decides to go searching for her sister to settle things between them. This takes her through a journey that reveals the true nature of their rivalries and raises a few more questions when she realizes that Craig plays a bigger role in her sister's life than she had expected. Jessica also starts to get better but she is not safe from harm. So she feels the need to go on a revenge rampage to put an end to the madness once and for all.::P.M. Salazar
